summary: Happy Birthday to this beautiful and immensely underrated album. This is the album that made me fall in love with Taylor and her...
body:
Happy Birthday to this beautiful and immensely underrated album. This is the album that made me fall in love with Taylor and her music, Our Song was the first one I listened to when I was about 4 (that’s when my mom started listening to her also). I knew there was something powerful in that girl singing about tears on her guitar and slamming doors, and I can tell you that 12 years later we all see her power and her huge heart. So let’s all listen to Stay Beautiful today and just celebrate Taylor Swift.

@taylorswift

summary: It's the debut album anniversary and I already know y'all are gonna forget all about her after like 10 minutes. But the debut is...
body: It’s the debut album anniversary and I already know y'all are gonna forget all about her after like 10 minutes. But the debut is my favorite. It’s the first album I ever bought with my own money. I remember listening to it on a CD player and listening to it over and over again. I related to invisible and tied together with a smile really helped me on days where I just wanted to give up. This album is what started my love for Taylor and her songwriting. Debut may be yeehaw now but it’s still one of the best country albums out there. The aesthetics and music videos were just amazing. Plus, this is when taylor opened for so many people and got her name out there. If anyone wants to watch really old performances of taylor in the debut era cmntexas on YouTube has a whole playlist.

summary: I love everyone who’s inspired me to write a song, whether you know it or not. I love anyone who has ever turned the volume up...
body:
I love everyone who’s inspired me to write a song, whether you know it or not. I love anyone who has ever turned the volume up when my song comes on the radio, anyone who has bought this album. Anyone who can sing along to my songs when I play them live. Anyone who’s ever requested my song on the radio, or ever remembered my name. If you ever see me in public, I want to meet you. I will thank you myself. You have let me into your life, and I will never be able to thank you enough for that.

Happy birthday to Taylor’s debut album, which turns 12 years old today

[I love Cold As You cuz the writing’s amazing, I love The Outside because its so honest and direct,  A Place in This World because its so heartfelt and Our Song because those lyrics are insanely clever, Tim McGraw has beautiful imagery and heart…]
